  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nLet's explore centralized push notifications as an *option* for all users, in order to improve retention rates.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nWe could bring back the old implementation of PNs, relying on Firebase.\r\n\r\nImplementation strategy is up to technical team.\r\n\r\nThe requirements for this issue are to conduct research and write a spec for how centralized PNs could work.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n1. Spec filed in https://github.com/status-im/specs. Spec should include:\r\n- Proposed solution\r\n- Pros/cons consideredâ€”for other solutions considered, as well\r\n- External components and/or dependencies\r\n- Privacy/security/risk evaluation\r\n\r\nOne requirement for the feature: these should be optional and toggled off by default.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n[Design explorations in progress](https://www.figma.com/file/bPS9GrvMr7LnH7vnkmuveQfd/Settings?node-id=1241%3A69)",
